paraphrase: What are the names of movies that do not have any ratings?
data.question: Find the titles of movies that don’t have any rating.
sql: SELECT title FROM movies WHERE rating IS NULL

paraphrase: What are names of movies that have a 'G' ratings?
data.question: Find the names of movies whose rating is ‘G’.
sql: SELECT title FROM movies WHERE rating  =  'G'

paraphrase: What are the movie titles for ones that are played in the Odeon theater?
data.question: Find the title of the movie that is played in the Odeon theater.
sql: SELECT T1.title FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie WHERE T2.name  =  'Odeon'

paraphrase: What are the names of the movies that are played in any theater and the name of the corresponding theater?
data.question: Find the names of movies that are played in any theater and the name of the corresponding theater.
sql: SELECT T1.title ,  T2.name FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie

paraphrase: How many movies had a 'G' rating?
data.question: Find the number of movies whose rating is ‘G’.
sql: SELECT count(*) FROM movies WHERE rating  =  'G'

paraphrase: How many movies are playing in theaters?
data.question: How many movies are playing across all theaters?
sql: SELECT count(*) FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie

paraphrase: How many different movies are playing?
data.question: How many distinct movies are on in theaters?
sql: SELECT count(DISTINCT T1.code) FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie

paraphrase: How many different movie theaters exist?
data.question: How many distinct movie theaters are there?
sql: SELECT count(DISTINCT name) FROM movietheaters

paraphrase: What is the rating of the movie what has a name including a word like 'Citizen'?
data.question: Find the rating of the movie whose name includes the word ‘Citizen’.
sql: SELECT rating FROM movies WHERE title LIKE '%Citizen%'

paraphrase: What are the names of the movie theaters that are playing 'G' or 'PG' rated movies?
data.question: Find the name of the cinemas that are playing movies with either rating ‘G’ or rating ‘PG’.
sql: SELECT title FROM movies WHERE rating  =  'G' OR rating  =  'PG'

paraphrase: What are the titles of all the movies that played at the Odeon or Imperial theater?
data.question: Find the name of the movies that are played in either cinema Odeon or Imperial.
sql: SELECT T1.title FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie WHERE T2.name  =  'Odeon' OR T2.name  =  'Imperial'

paraphrase: What movie is playing at both the Odeon and Imperial theater?
data.question: Find the name of the movie that is on in both Odeon and Imperial theaters.
sql: SELECT T1.title FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie WHERE T2.name  =  'Odeon' INTERSECT SELECT T1.title FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie WHERE T2.name  =  'Imperial'

paraphrase: What are the names of every movie that is not playing at the Odeon theater?
data.question: Find the name of all movies that are not played in Odeon theater.
sql: SELECT title FROM movies EXCEPT SELECT T1.title FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie WHERE T2.name  =  'Odeon'

paraphrase: What are the movie names in alphabetical order?
data.question: List in alphabetical order the titles of all movies.
sql: SELECT title FROM movies ORDER BY title

paraphrase: What are the movie names sorted by rating?
data.question: Find the titles of all movies sorted by their ratings.
sql: SELECT title FROM movies ORDER BY rating

paraphrase: What is the name of the theater playing the most movies?
data.question: Find the name of the theater that is playing the most number of movies.
sql: SELECT name FROM movietheaters GROUP BY name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

paraphrase: What is the name of the film playing at the most number of theaters?
data.question: Find the name of the movie that is played in the most number of theaters.
sql: SELECT T1.title FROM movies AS T1 JOIN movietheaters AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.movie GROUP BY T1.title ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

paraphrase: How many movies exist for each rating?
data.question: Find the number of movies in each rating.
sql: SELECT count(*) ,  rating FROM movies GROUP BY rating

paraphrase: How many movies have a rating that is not null?
How many movies are there for each non-NULL rating?
data.question: Find the number of movies whose rating is not null.
sql: SELECT count(*) ,  rating FROM movies WHERE rating IS NOT NULL GROUP BY rating

paraphrase: What are the names of every theater with at least one movie playing?
data.question: Find the name of theaters that has at least one movie playing.
sql: SELECT name FROM movietheaters GROUP BY name HAVING count(*)  >=  1

paraphrase: What are the names of all cinemas not showing any movies?
data.question: Select the name of all movie theaters that are not currently showing a movie.
sql: SELECT DISTINCT name FROM MovieTheaters WHERE Movie IS NULL

paraphrase: What are all of the movie names?
data.question: Select the title of all movies.

data.question: Show all the distinct ratings in the database.

data.question: Show all information of all unrated movies.

data.question: Show the titles of movies not currently being shown in any theaters.
